stylometry:
Fixed costs models- is when you want to find how much profit you can make based on costs that you cannot change 
Set covering models- is when you have an area you need to cover and you want to find out how to sufficiently cover that area using the least amount of hubs.
We are trying to get the most amout of production/money using the least amount of materials/costs and it is important because you need to know how to do that in order to not waste materials or resources and be able to still be successful.
An example of a set covering model would be finding the minimal amount of firestations that a city needs to be able to get to any point in that city in a given amount of time.
